
[1]antique

   ANTIQUE, a. antee'k. [L. antiquus, probably from ante.]

   1. Old; ancient; of genuine antiquity; in this sense it usually refers
   to the flourishing ages of Greece and Rome; as an antique statue.

   2. Old, as it respects the present age, or a modern period of time; of
   old fashion, as an antique robe.

   3. Odd; wild; fanciful; more generally written antic.

     ANTIQUE, n. antee'k. In general, any thing very old; but in a more
      limited sense, the remains of ancient artists, as busts, statues,
       paintings and vases, the works of Grecian and Roman antiquity.
     __________________________________________________________________

